<% content_for :head do %><title>Contexts — Enliterator</title><% end %>

<h1>Contexts <span class="muted" style="font-weight:400; font-size:.95rem">— collections within collections</span></h1>
<p class="muted" style="max-width:64ch">
  A context is a <strong>lens</strong>: an item belongs to the whole collection and to any number of
  labeled sub-collections, and each context reads its members through its own facets and vocabulary,
  <em>inheriting</em> its ancestors'. Claims live per context and read cumulatively — the finding-aid
  principle: an item understood through its place in the hierarchy plus its own description.
  Select any context here (or in the nav switcher) to view every surface through it.
</p>

<% if @rows.empty? %>
  <div class="card">
    <p class="muted">No contexts seeded yet — the whole collection is one root context. Create
    <code>Enliterator::Context</code> records (an <code>ancestry</code> tree) and place members with
    <code>record.place_in_context!(ctx)</code>; declare per-context facets with the staffing policy's
    <code>context "key" do … end</code> blocks.</p>
  </div>
<% else %>
  <div class="card">
    <table>
      <tr><th>context</th><th>own facets <span class="muted" style="font-weight:400">(what tends here)</span></th><th>members</th><th>live claims</th><th>tending visits</th></tr>
      <%# Root row: the whole collection (the NULL scope, rule 1) %>
      <tr>
        <td><strong><%= link_to "whole collection", root_path(context: "root") %></strong>
            <% unless current_context %><span class="chip tier">viewing</span><% end %></td>
        <td class="samples"><%= @policy.facets_declared_in(nil).join(", ").presence || "—" %></td>
        <td class="muted">all</td>
        <td><%= @stats[:claims][nil].to_i %></td>
        <td><%= @stats[:visits][nil].to_i %></td>
      </tr>
      <% @rows.each do |ctx, depth| %>
        <tr>
          <td style="padding-left: <%= 0.5 + depth * 1.4 %>rem">
            <strong><%= link_to ctx.name, root_path(context: ctx.key) %></strong>
            <code class="muted" style="font-size:.75rem"><%= ctx.key %></code>
            <% if current_context&.id == ctx.id %><span class="chip tier">viewing</span><% end %>
          </td>
          <td class="samples"><%= @policy.facets_declared_in(ctx.key).join(", ").presence || "inherits only" %></td>
          <td><%= @stats[:members][ctx.id].to_i %></td>
          <td><%= @stats[:claims][ctx.id].to_i %></td>
          <td><%= @stats[:visits][ctx.id].to_i %></td>
        </tr>
      <% end %>
    </table>
  </div>
  <p class="muted samples" style="max-width:64ch">
    "Own facets" are the facets <em>declared</em> in a context — what a tending pass runs there. A
    context also inherits every ancestor's facets, and its members are read in light of root claims.
    Counts are each context's own scope (root counts = root-scope rows, not the rolled-up union).
    Clicking a context name opens Status viewed through it.
  </p>
<% end %>
